    <div class="ms-3 me-2" style="text-align: justify;">
      <p><b>Notes:</b></p>
      <ol type="1">
        <li>
          <p>Requirements are based on aggregate amount of in-force insurance on any one's life.</p>
        </li>
        <li>
          <p>Terminology for routine medical requirements:</p>
          <ol type="a">
            <li><p></p>FME - Full Medical Examination (FME form shall be accomplished and duly signed by the examining doctor and signed by the applicant for insurance)</p></li>
            <li><p>MUR - Chemical and Microscopic Urinalysis</p></li>
            <li><p>CXR - Chest X-Ray result (with film and interpretation)</p></li>
            <li><p>ECG - Electrocardiogram (with complete tracing and interpretation)</p></li>
            <li>
              <p>BEX - Blood Examination</p>
              <p>BEX (A)- Fasting Blood Sugar, BUN, Creatinine, Cholesterol, Uric Acid, CBC</p>
              <p>BEX (B)- Fasting Blood Sugar, BUN, Creatinine, Cholesterol, Uric Acid, CBC, SGOT, SGPT, HIV, Triglycerides</p>
              <p>BEX (C)- Fasting Blood Sugar, BUN, Creatinine, Cholesterol, Uric Acid, CBC, SGOT, SGPT, HIV, Triglycerides, HBSAG, Anti-HBS</p>
            </li>
            <li><p>TMT - Treadmill Test</p></li>
          </ol>
        </li>
        <li>
          <p>Blood Exam - 1 & 2 has an <b>8 to 12 hours</b> fasting requirement. <b>(NO Fasting No Exam)</b></p>
        </li>
        <li>
          <p>All medical examination results have a validity period of <b>six (6) months</b>. If a proposed insured fails to finish or submit all medical documents within the <b>six (6) months</b> period, he will be required to submit new medical results.</p>
        </li>
        <li>
          <p>Any amount in excess of the non-medical limit will not be covered by insurance unless all medical requirements are met.</p>
        </li>
        <li>
          <p>Latest Financial Statement, current ITR & Investigation Report shall automatically be required to applications with more than 10 million of sum insured.</p>
        </li>
      </ol>

      <p><b>1 CISP reserves the right to require additional medical or laboratory tests should the declaration in the Applicant's Health Statement so warrants. No coverage shall take effect for those required to undergo medical examination/s unless there is a written approval of coverage from 1 CISP.</b></p>
    </div>

    <p><b>4.7 Schedule of Premium Remittance and Submission of Summary Report and Application Forms.</b> The <i>Summary Report,</i> individual <i>LPPI Application forms</i> and <i>Total Premium</i> collected by the COOPERATIVE for the LOAN releases during the month shall be submitted to 1 CISP <b>on or before the 15<sup>th</sup> day of the succeeding month</b>, if that day falls on Saturday, Sunday or Holiday, the next business day.</p>
    <p>1 CISP shall not be liable for any claim filed in case the COOPERATIVE remits the premium and submits the summary report and application forms <b>beyond thirty one (31) calendar days after the month of loan releases.</b></p>
  </div>

  <p class="me-3" style="text-align: justify;">
  <b>5.<u class="ms-3">Claim Requirements.</u></b> All claims shall be filed together with reasonable proofs of death and all supporting information. Notice of claim shall be submitted to 1 CISP within thirty one (31) calendar days and proof of loss within ninety (90) days from the date of death, except when it can be shown that failer to submit the notice and proof within such time is due to valid reason.
  </p>

  <p class="me-3 ms-4" style="text-align: justify;">
    1 CISP, upon receipt of a notice of claim, will furnish to the Claimant such forms as are usually required by 1 CISP for filing proofs of loss. All certificates, information and evidence, other than the usual forms, which 1 CISP shall reasonably require in support of a claim.
  </p>
